    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Definitely Dutch</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Morton J Miller letter on July 30 travel article notes Leiden, Netherlands, is birthplace of Leyden jar, early device used to store small amounts of electricity for lab experiments (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Christopher Hall's article ''Unmistakably Dutch'' (July 30), about Leiden, the Netherlands, was quite informative. But here is another bit of the city's history: Leiden was the birthplace of the famous Leyden (Leiden) jar, an early device used to store small amounts of electricity for laboratory experiments. It probably did more to spread the name of Leiden than any other of the city's numerous accomplishments.</p>
        <p>MORTON J. MILLER  Allentown, Pa.</p>
      </block>
